content:
A value list entity provides a way to extract the entity if thereâ€™s an exact match to a value or a synonym in a list of values.

Einstein Bots is available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience. Setup for Einstein Bots is available in Lightning Experience.
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

To build and manage Einstein Bots:
Customize Application
OR
Modify Metadata
OR
Manage Bots

For example, you can create a value list entity called Color with three values and their synonyms. The bot can recognize any value list value as a match for the color value.

From the Bot Builder menu, click Entities.
Click New.
Provide an entity name and select Value List.
Save the new entity.
Add each value and corresponding value list.
Save the entity.
title: Value List Entity in Einstein Bots
